        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add Codex pace headroom hint",
        "body": "## Owner decision — product-tone hold\n\n**Decision requested:** Should the menu proactively tell a user `Try 1.5x!` when the conservative headroom model says their remaining quota can support it, and should the minimum historical-week threshold be user-configurable in Advanced settings?\n\n**Tradeoff:** The wording turns safe headroom into an immediate, useful action and the setting exposes a real confidence threshold. The copy can feel prescriptive or celebratory in a utility menu, while the setting adds another expert-facing control.\n\n**Recommendation:** **Land as written** with the conservative gate and current copy for one release. Keep this PR unmerged only for the owner's tone/settings acceptance and exact-head CI; if the tone is declined, change the copy to `1.5x headroom` without changing the model.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Show `Try 1.5x!` when Codex usage has more than 15% reserve and remaining quota supports at least 1.5x the projected remaining burn.\n- Add an Advanced setting for the minimum number of complete Codex weeks used to enable historical pace, defaulting to 3 and allowing 2-8.\n- Keep Ollama cookie diagnostics out of this PR so the pace/settings decision stays independently reviewable.\n\n## Behavior and tradeoff\n\nThe hint appears only when the quota is projected to last until reset, reserve exceeds 15%, and the safe remaining-burn multiplier is at least 1.5. Linear and workday pace use remaining capacity versus usage projected across the remaining window; historical pace uses remaining capacity versus the remaining expected historical curve.\n\nThe current `Try 1.5x!` wording is intentionally prominent and actionable, but it is a product-tone choice. Recommendation: keep the conservative gate and use the current copy for one release; if it feels too celebratory in the menu, change only the copy to `1.5x headroom` without changing the model.\n\n## Maintainer preparation\n\n- Split the unrelated Ollama access-denied change from this branch.\n- Fixed late-window headroom math and added linear, historical, UI, and CLI regression coverage.\n- Fixed Italian localization and repository formatting failures present on the contributor head.\n- Packaged the debug app and verified the Advanced setting in the live bundle.\n- Generated a redacted synthetic three-state card fixture for ahead/on-track/behind comparison. No real account usage is represented by that fixture.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `make check`\n- `make test` (43 shards)\n- focused pace, historical pace, CLI snapshot, localization, and Ollama regression suites\n- `CODEXBAR_SIGNING=adhoc ./Scripts/package_app.sh debug`\n- autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nThe debug bundle requested macOS app-data access during live-account rendering. That permission was not granted; packaged UI proof is limited to the setting and synthetic redacted card states.\n",
